rfsn_v11 — Alembic Migration Environment
=========================================

This directory contains the Alembic migration environment for the rfsn_v11
telemetry schema.  The ``telemetry_events`` table stores every field of the
``TelemetryEvent`` dataclass (``rfsn_v11/telemetry.py``).

Quick start
-----------

1. Install dependencies::

       pip install alembic sqlalchemy

2. Set the database URL (optional — defaults to SQLite)::

       export RFSN_DB_URL=postgresql://user:pass@localhost/rfsn_v11

3. Apply all pending migrations::

       alembic -c rfsn_v11/alembic.ini upgrade head

4. Generate a new migration after schema changes::

       alembic -c rfsn_v11/alembic.ini revision --autogenerate -m "describe change"

5. Show current revision::

       alembic -c rfsn_v11/alembic.ini current

Directory layout
----------------

alembic/
    env.py          — Migration environment (reads RFSN_DB_URL).
    README          — This file.
    versions/
        0001_create_telemetry_events.py
                    — Initial migration: creates ``telemetry_events`` table.

Configuration
-------------

``alembic.ini`` (one level above this directory) controls:

- ``script_location``  — points here (``rfsn_v11/alembic``).
- ``sqlalchemy.url``   — default SQLite URL; override with ``RFSN_DB_URL``.

The ``env.py`` always prefers ``RFSN_DB_URL`` over the ini value, so CI and
production environments never need to edit the ini file.
